1. MOST COMMON (Best Option)
10.0.0.0/16

Kyu best?

Simple

Yaad rehne wala

Large (65,536 IPs)

Subnet banana easy (/24, /20, /28 etc.)

Har project me use ho sakta

→ Real world me 80% VPCs यही use karti hain.



Yes Faisal, 10.0.0.0/24 (public) + 10.0.1.0/24 (private)
10.0.0.0/24



2. General Rules for Subnet CIDR
✔ Public = usually /24
✔ Private = usually /24
✔ DB = /24
✔ NAT / LB = /28
✔ ALWAYS different availability zones me

Requirement	Allowed?	Notes
Public + Private in same AZ	✅ Yes	Perfect design
Use same CIDR  for multiple public subnets	❌ No	Each subnet must have unique CIDR
Use same CIDR  for multiple private subnets	❌ No	Each subnet must have unique CIDR
Use same CIDR  for multiple public and private subnets	❌ No	Each subnet must have unique CIDR



3. Final Summary (Absolutely Correct)
⭐ If VPC = 10.0.0.0/16

➡ Subnets 10.0.0.0/24, 10.0.1.0/24, 10.0.2.0/24 …

⭐ If VPC = 10.1.0.0/16

➡ Subnets 10.1.0.0/24, 10.1.1.0/24, 10.1.2.0/24 …

⭐ If VPC = 10.5.0.0/16

➡ Subnets 10.5.0.0/24, 10.5.1.0/24, 10.5.2.0/24 …


⭐ If VPC = 10.0.0.0/16

➡ Valid subnets:
10.0.0.0/24 → 10.0.255.0/24
(Yani 10.0.X.0/24 where X = 0 to 255)

⭐ If VPC = 10.1.0.0/16

➡ Valid subnets:
10.1.0.0/24 → 10.1.255.0/24
(Yani 10.1.X.0/24 where X = 0 to 255)

⭐ If VPC = 10.5.0.0/16

➡ Valid subnets:
10.5.0.0/24 → 10.5.255.0/24
(Yani 10.5.X.0/24 where X = 0 to 255)


⭐ VPC CIDR Rule
✔ Valid VPC CIDR = 10.X.0.0 /16 → /28

Where:

X = 0 to 255

Last 2 octets = 0.0
